com.vmware.vcenter.namespace_management.supervisors.identity

Class ProvidersTypes.UpdateSpec

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.vmware.vcenter.namespace_management.supervisors.identity.ProvidersTypes.UpdateSpec
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    com.vmware.vapi.bindings.StaticStructure, com.vmware.vapi.bindings.Structure, java.io.Serializable
    Enclosing interface:
    ProvidersTypes

    public static final class ProvidersTypes.UpdateSpec
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable, com.vmware.vapi.bindings.StaticStructure
    The UpdateSpec class contains the specification required to update the configuration of an identity provider used with a Supervisor. This class was added in vSphere API 8.0.0.1.

      • getAdditionalAuthorizeParameters

        public java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.String> getAdditionalAuthorizeParameters()
        Any additional parameters to be sent to the upstream identity provider during the authorize request in the OAuth2 authorization code flow. One use case is to pass in a default tenant ID if you have a multi-tenant identity provider. For instance, with VMware's Cloud Services Platform, if your organization ID is 'long-form-org-id', the 'orgLink' parameter can be set to "/csp/gateway/am/api/orgs/long-form-org-id" to allow users logging in to leverage that organization. This property was added in vSphere API 8.0.0.1. If null, the additional parameters will not be updated.
        Returns:
        The current value of the property.

      • setAdditionalAuthorizeParameters

        public void setAdditionalAuthorizeParameters(java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.String> additionalAuthorizeParameters)
        Any additional parameters to be sent to the upstream identity provider during the authorize request in the OAuth2 authorization code flow. One use case is to pass in a default tenant ID if you have a multi-tenant identity provider. For instance, with VMware's Cloud Services Platform, if your organization ID is 'long-form-org-id', the 'orgLink' parameter can be set to "/csp/gateway/am/api/orgs/long-form-org-id" to allow users logging in to leverage that organization. This property was added in vSphere API 8.0.0.1. If null, the additional parameters will not be updated.
        Parameters:
        additionalAuthorizeParameters - New value for the property.
